{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c17a9b03-66f4-4402-882c-095a8deb2c25","content":"Run **`dotnet workload update`**.\n\n- **`dotnet workload update`** — downloads and installs the latest versions of all installed workloads, aligning them with your current SDK. This is what you need after an SDK update.\n- **`dotnet workload repair`** — reinstalls the *same* versions already recorded; it fixes corrupted installations but won't pull newer packages.\n\nAfter updating:\n\n```bash\ndotnet workload update\ndotnet build\n```\n\nIf the build still fails, check that your `.csproj` targets a compatible `net8.0-*` / `net9.0-*` TFM for the new SDK version.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"93a444de-1471-429f-9197-346d2e5cdb82","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the difference between `dotnet workload update` and `dotnet workload repair` to fix a .NET MAUI build issue after an SDK update. This is a general knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to look at any files.","outputTokens":224,"requestId":"5013:739A4:1B5BC9F:1E5C153:69FA8FAC"},"id":"9ee4e257-5747-4885-b1a7-91d53fdbfd7c","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:47:47.594Z","parentId":"fed4a442-1b35-4a48-830c-eecaae113653"}
